## Discipline: Mandatory Behaviors

### Blast-Radius Discipline

**Before modifying any symbol**, read its impact files:

```bash
{{ hints.vfs_analysis() }}
```

Never modify a function signature, rename a symbol, or delete code without first understanding who depends on it. One read each — they include inline code context.

### Filter by Kind

```bash
ls {{ paths.by_kind("file." ~ ext, "fn") }}       # all functions
ls {{ paths.by_kind("file." ~ ext, "struct") }}   # all structs
ls {{ paths.by_kind("file." ~ ext, "impl") }}     # all impl blocks
```

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-pattern | Correct approach |
|-|-|
| `Read file.{{ ext }}` (raw file read) | `Read {{ paths.sym_overview("file." ~ ext) }}` then targeted symbol |
| `Grep "fn process" src/` | `ls {{ paths.by_kind("file." ~ ext, "fn") }}` or `{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` |
| `Grep "process" src/` for callers | `Read {{ paths.sym_md("file." ~ ext, "process", "CALLERS") }}` |
| Full file read for imports | `Read {{ paths.imports("file." ~ ext, ext) }}` |
| Editing raw source files | Edit `@/symbols/` bodies (tree-sitter validated) |
| Grep + manual line math for symbol | `readlink {{ paths.at_line("file." ~ ext, 42) }}` (instant) |
| Reading N files for call sites | `{{ FILE_CALLERS }}` has inline code context for all sites |
| Modifying without checking callers | **Always** read `{{ FILE_CALLERS }}` first |
| Using symbol paths after a write without re-reading | Re-read `{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` after writes — the symbol table may have changed |
| `Bash(cat {{ paths.file_overview() }})` for single reads | Use the **Read tool** — it's the default for all single-path `@/` reads |
| Guessing path variations on `ENOENT` | `ls symbols/` or `{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` to find the current name |
| Sequential direct writes to 2+ symbols | Batch edit staging — atomic, validated |
